cs.CR, cs.HC, cs.CY, cs.MM, cs.CV 

The paper introduces a new behavioral biometric for continuous authentication of smartphone users. It involves capturing subtle micro-movement and orientation dynamics resulting from how a user grasps, holds, and taps on the smartphone. This falls under the category of cybersecurity (cs.CR) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The paper also involves data analysis and machine learning techniques for authentication and biometric key generation, which could fall under the categories of computer vision (cs.CV), multimedia (cs.MM), and cyber-physical systems (cs.CY).
